      "date": "2016-04-01 14:23:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nWhy is this ioctl (and not OBD_IOC_GETFILESTRIPE) being deprecated?  We should be providing a reliable set of user space ioctl for applications to use. \n\nIf an application is currently using this ioctl directly, then the developer is clearly not going to want to switch to using \"lfs getstripe\".   If we are going to deprecate this then we need to replace it with another method that is better for applications to use, not worse.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
